during `vectorizeGEPIndices` when it calls `tryToVectorizeList`, which builds a
tree and then attempts to vectorize it. However, something in the tree building
process is creating an invalid TreeEntry.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\n\nThe
root cause appears to be in the `vectorizeGEPIndices` function. When processing
GEP indices, the code creates a bundle of index values and passes them to
