processing GEP indices\n- The `all_of(E->Scalars, ...)` condition fails because
`E->Scalars` is empty\n\nThe problem is that the assertion assumes that if we
don't have gathered loads, then we must have valid scalars from the same basic
block. However, in this case, we have an empty scalars vector, which violates
both conditions.\n\nThe issue likely stems from how GEP indices are processed.
The bundle contains GEP index values (zext, sext instructions), but during tree
